{"info": {"author": "", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# pysisyphus\n[![Documentation Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/pysisyphus/badge/?version=master)](https://pysisyphus.readthedocs.io/en/master/?badge=master)\n[![build](https://github.com/eljost/pysisyphus/workflows/Python%20application/badge.svg)](https://github.com/eljost/pysisyphus/actions)\n[![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/eljost/pysisyphus/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/eljost/pysisyphus)\n[![License: GPL v3](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-GPLv3-blue.svg)](https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0)\n[![DOI](https://zenodo.org/badge/96281078.svg)](https://zenodo.org/badge/latestdoi/96281078)\n\n`pysisyphus` is a software-suite for the exploration of potential energy surfaces in ground-\nand **excited states**. It implements several methods to search for stationary points\n(minima and first order saddle points) and the calculation of minimum energy paths by means\nof IRC and Chain of States methods like Nudged Elastic Band and Growing String.\nFurthermore it provides tools to easily analyze & modify geometries (aligning, translating, **interpolating**, ...) and to visualize the calculation results/progress.\n\nThe required energies, gradients and hessians are calculated by calling external quantum chemistry codes. `pysisyphus` can also be used as a library to implement custom quantum chemistry workflows.\n\nIf any issues arise please open an issue and I'll try to fix it if possible and my time permits it. Contrubtions are welcome, so feel free to submit a PR.\n\n**This software is still work in progress. Use at your own risk.**\n\n## Example\n\nFully internal coordinate transition state search for the famous alanine dipeptide isomerization reaction using the xtb calculator and the growing string method.\n\n[![asciicast](https://asciinema.org/a/300731.svg)](https://asciinema.org/a/300731)\n\n## Documentation\n\nPlease have a look at the [documentation](https://pysisyphus.readthedocs.io/en/dev/).\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/eljost/pysisyphus", "keywords": "", "license": "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "maintainer": "Johannes Steinmetzer", "maintainer_email": "johannes.steinmetzer@uni-jena.de", "name": "pysisyphus", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pysisyphus/", "platform": "unix", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pysisyphus/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/eljost/pysisyphus"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pysisyphus/0.4/", "requires_dist": ["attrs", "autograd", "distributed", "h5py", "numpy", "matplotlib", "natsort", "dask", "pandas", "pytest", "pytest-harvest", "pyyaml", "rmsd", "sympy", "scipy", "ase ; extra == 'ase'", "pyscf (>=1.7.0) ; extra == 'pyscf'", "qcengine (>=0.13.0) ; extra == 'qcengine'"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "Python suite for exploring potential energy surfaces.", "version": "0.4", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>pysisyphus</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://pysisyphus.readthedocs.io/en/master/?badge=master\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Documentation Status\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/1e5b1f8436e4c3328ecb8076af2e2088edf18f94/68747470733a2f2f72656164746865646f63732e6f72672f70726f6a656374732f707973697379706875732f62616467652f3f76657273696f6e3d6d6173746572\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/eljost/pysisyphus/actions\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"build\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/f75f57e6da581fbff802942ebecc33ea2357f5d3/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f656c6a6f73742f707973697379706875732f776f726b666c6f77732f507974686f6e2532306170706c69636174696f6e2f62616467652e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://codecov.io/gh/eljost/pysisyphus\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"codecov\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/028e59344dd0127d0116c23582026276eb704ccd/68747470733a2f2f636f6465636f762e696f2f67682f656c6a6f73742f707973697379706875732f6272616e63682f6d61737465722f67726170682f62616467652e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"License: GPL v3\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/8de17537dd1659a5a076ce547de301e27c839e67/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f4c6963656e73652d47504c76332d626c75652e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://zenodo.org/badge/latestdoi/96281078\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"DOI\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/ec3359c6d6f2c86337942dd849fe0a8b6a765fbb/68747470733a2f2f7a656e6f646f2e6f72672f62616467652f39363238313037382e737667\"></a></p>\n<p><code>pysisyphus</code> is a software-suite for the exploration of potential energy surfaces in ground-\nand <strong>excited states</strong>. It implements several methods to search for stationary points\n(minima and first order saddle points) and the calculation of minimum energy paths by means\nof IRC and Chain of States methods like Nudged Elastic Band and Growing String.\nFurthermore it provides tools to easily analyze &amp; modify geometries (aligning, translating, <strong>interpolating</strong>, ...) and to visualize the calculation results/progress.</p>\n<p>The required energies, gradients and hessians are calculated by calling external quantum chemistry codes. <code>pysisyphus</code> can also be used as a library to implement custom quantum chemistry workflows.</p>\n<p>If any issues arise please open an issue and I'll try to fix it if possible and my time permits it. Contrubtions are welcome, so feel free to submit a PR.</p>\n<p><strong>This software is still work in progress. Use at your own risk.</strong></p>\n<h2>Example</h2>\n<p>Fully internal coordinate transition state search for the famous alanine dipeptide isomerization reaction using the xtb calculator and the growing string method.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://asciinema.org/a/300731\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"asciicast\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/1dd3e4da9bd63944f18b7164148bb6af1a9a56b5/68747470733a2f2f61736369696e656d612e6f72672f612f3330303733312e737667\"></a></p>\n<h2>Documentation</h2>\n<p>Please have a look at the <a href=\"https://pysisyphus.readthedocs.io/en/dev/\" rel=\"nofollow\">documentation</a>.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7075140, "releases": {"0.0.10": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "4958f318489993d1d9307d73ff98be60", "sha256": "a4ea054d2ba39e7a657068691ccad35f0dd7d5b84ab38a59432f65aebea6e810"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pysisyphus-0.0.10.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "4958f318489993d1d9307d73ff98be60", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 52955, "upload_time": "2017-12-11T15:33:02", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2017-12-11T15:33:02.645042Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/3d/ea/83df6dff356ed9d7aae9cb34642e4cd37242929378450a375cf531de5be9/pysisyphus-0.0.10.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.2": [], "0.0.20": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "564ba8e88a9d23771e7b2f7b8df45f7a", "sha256": "69c5975c992ad90314e48b35267116c51e282b592e88c389a57e6f9f0aef5b64"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pysisyphus-0.0.20.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "564ba8e88a9d23771e7b2f7b8df45f7a", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 74213, "upload_time": "2018-03-14T13:42:58", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2018-03-14T13:42:58.948997Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/91/b1/1d67b5f20b00d77625edfb28cd43ae3963d47b936eca4f6568b581d57951/pysisyphus-0.0.20.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.3": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "b190eeec7f2c28e8263105850d248dd0", "sha256": "4276a8ebd749ac97f84f18aca38f917ed2e814feb70622